│ `TTI::getShuffleCost` -> `X86TTIImpl::getShuffleCost` -> `improveShuffleKindFromMask` ->   │
│ `isSelectMask` -> `isSingleSourceMask` -> `isSingleSourceMaskImpl`.\n\nThe crash occurs    │
│ during the cost analysis of a potential transformation, specifically when checking if the  │
│ shuffle can be simplified. The reproducer shows a `shufflevector` that takes two `<4 x     │
│ float>` vectors and produces a `<2 x float>` vector. The shuffle mask is `<i32 4, i32      │
│ 7>`.\n\n### 3. Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe root cause lies in `foldShuffleOfSelects` when   │
│ it calls `TTI.getShuffleCost`. This function attempts to determine the cost of a new,      │
│ hypothetical shuffle instruction that would result from folding the selects.\n\nThe logic  │
│ in `foldShuffleOfSelects` constructs a new shuffle mask (`NewMask`) and determines the new │
│ source vector type (`SrcVTy`). In the provided reproducer, the original shuffle sources    │
│ are `<4 x float>`, and the result is `<2 x float>`. The logic correctly deduces that the   │
│ new sources for the folded shuffle would be `<2 x float>` vectors.\n\nHowever, when it     │
│ calls `TTI.getShuffleCost`, it passes `SrcVTy` (the new `<2 x float>` type) but provides   │
│ the original shuffle mask (`<i32 4, i32 7>`). The `getShuffleCost` function and its        │
│ callees, including `isSelectMask`, operate under the assumption that the mask indices are  │
│ valid for the provided source vector type.\n\nThe function `isSelectMask` receives         │
│ `NumElts = 2` (from the new source type `<2 x float>`) and the mask `<4, 7>`. It then      │
│ attempts to check if the first `NumElts` (2) elements of the mask correspond to a valid    │
│ single-source shuffle. It calls `isSingleSourceMask` with `Mask.slice(0, 2)` and `NumElts  │
│ = 2`. The sliced mask contains `{4, 7}`. Inside `isSingleSourceMaskImpl`, the assertion    │
│ fails because the mask element `4` is not less than `NumOpElts * 2` (which is `2 * 2 =     │
│ 4`).\n\nThe fundamental mistake is passing a shuffle mask that is incompatible with the    │
│ vector type used for cost analysis. The mask indices `{4, 7}` are valid for the original   │
│ `<4 x float>` sources but are out of bounds for the hypothetical `<2 x float>`             │
│ sources.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\n\nThe fix is to ensure that the shuffle mask    │
│ passed to `TTI.getShuffleCost` is valid for the source vector type being considered. Since │
│ the existing `NewMask` is constructed based on the original vector width, we should use    │
│ the original source vector type (`OrigSrcVTy`) for the cost analysis instead of the new,   │
│ narrower `SrcVTy`.\n\n```cpp\n// In llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp\n\n//  │
│ Proposed Edit Point 1\n// File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp\n// Lines: │
│ 2059-2061\n// Original:\n  if (TTI.getShuffleCost(TargetTransformInfo::SK_PermuteTwoSrc,   │
│ SrcVTy, NewMask,\n                         TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput) >= ShuffleCost)\n     │
│ return false;\n// Proposed Change:\n  if                                                   │
│ (TTI.getShuffleCost(TargetTransformInfo::SK_PermuteTwoSrc, OrigSrcVTy,\n                   │
│ NewMask, TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput) >= ShuffleCost)\n    return false;\n```\n\nBy changing  │
│ `SrcVTy` to `OrigSrcVTy` in the `getShuffleCost` call, we provide a vector type that is    │
│ consistent with the indices in `NewMask`. In this case, `OrigSrcVTy` is `<4 x float>`, so  │
│ `NumElts` will be 4, and the mask indices `{4, 7}` will be correctly validated against the │
│ range `[0, 2 * 4 - 1] = [0, 7]`.\n\n### 5. Conclusion\n\nThe crash was caused by a logical │
│ error in `foldShuffleOfSelects` where an inconsistent shuffle mask and vector type were    │
│ used for cost analysis, leading to an assertion failure in a downstream utility function.  │
│ The proposed fix corrects this by providing the original source vector type, which matches │
│ the structure of the generated shuffle mask, to the cost model. This ensures that the      │
│ analysis is performed with valid parameters, preventing the crash and allowing the         │
│ optimization to proceed correctly."                                                        │
│ }                                                                                          │
