│ An analysis of the bug report indicates a crash in the `vector-combine` pass. The root     │
│ cause is an assertion failure in `isSingleSourceMaskImpl`, triggered when                  │
│ `foldShuffleOfSelects` in `VectorCombine.cpp` calls `TTI.getShuffleCost`. This call is     │
│ made with a shuffle mask that is incompatible with the provided vector type, leading to an │
│ out-of-bounds access attempt.                                                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ Specifically, `foldShuffleOfSelects` attempts to evaluate the cost of a potential          │
│ transformation. It constructs a new shuffle mask (`NewMask`) based on the original source  │
│ vectors but then pairs this mask with a new, narrower vector type (`SrcVTy`) when calling  │
│ `getShuffleCost`. The mask indices are valid for the original, wider vector type but not   │
│ for the new, narrower one.                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to provide the correct, original source vector type (`OrigSrcVTy`) to the       │
│ `getShuffleCost` function, ensuring that the mask indices are validated against the        │
│ appropriate vector width.                                                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now apply this fix.                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ <tool_call>                                                                                │
│ {                                                                                          │
│   "name": "edit",                                                                          │
│   "args": {                                                                                │
│     "file": "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp",                             │
│     "old": "  if (TTI.getShuffleCost(TargetTransformInfo::SK_PermuteTwoSrc, SrcVTy,        │
│ NewMask,\n                         TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput) >= ShuffleCost)\n    return   │
│ false;",                                                                                   │
│     "new": "  if (TTI.getShuffleCost(TargetTransformInfo::SK_PermuteTwoSrc, OrigSrcVTy,\n  │
│ NewMask, TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput) >= ShuffleCost)\n    return false;"                     │
│   }                                                                                        │
│ }                                                                                          │
│ </tool_call>                                                                               │
│ The change has been applied. Now, I will verify the fix by running the tests.              │
│                                                                                            │
│ <tool_call>                                                                                │
│ {                                                                                          │
│   "name": "test",                                                                          │
│   "args": {}                                                                               │
│ }                                                                                          │
│ </tool_call>                                                                               │
